---
id: org.dxos.plugin.image
name: ImagePlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

An image-creation plugin for `DXOS` Composer. An `ImageArtifact` pairs a
prompt (`Instructions`) with an ordered set of `Image`s — each either
**generated** (remote URL) or **uploaded** (a `File.File` blob). The user
authors the prompt, generates against a pluggable `ImageGenerationService`
and/or uploads their own images, and reviews the results — either one image
at a time or all together in a gallery.

The plugin is **provider-agnostic**: it defines the `ImageGenerationService`
abstraction and never talks to a specific image API. Concrete providers
(e.g. `plugin-ideogram`) register an implementation and manage their own
credentials via the Connector system. Credentialed access is resolved at
generation time through `CredentialsService` keyed by the provider's
`source` (the same `AccessToken.source` a Connector stores), so the
Image plugin depends on no provider for generation; the toolbar surfaces
the provider's `ConnectorAuth` "Connect" button until a credential exists.

The gallery view uses a masonry gallery component **vendored from
`plugin-gallery`** (`useImageUrl` + `@dxos/react-ui-masonry`) generalized to
render **both** remote-URL images and `File.File` blobs.
`plugin-image` **supersedes and replaces `plugin-gallery`, which is
deleted in this milestone.**

## Scope of this milestone

This milestone spans **two** new packages. Per convention the authoritative
spec lives here; the `plugin-ideogram` additions are captured as a
cross-package section and `plugin-ideogram` also ships its own `PLUGIN.mdl`.

| Package             | Additions                                                                                                   |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `plugin-image`| New UI plugin: `ImageArtifact` + `Image` types, the `ImageGenerationService` abstraction, the `generateImage` op, upload, the `ImageArtifactArticle` surface, and a vendored masonry gallery (this spec's home). |
| `plugin-ideogram`   | New headless plugin: a Connector for `ideogram.ai` (API-key credential form) + an `ImageGenerationService` implementation. Owns its own `PLUGIN.mdl`. |
| `plugin-gallery`    | **Deleted** — superseded by `plugin-image` (unregistered from composer-app; package + root-aggregate entries removed). |

