## Types

```mdl
type Image
  desc: >
    One image held by an ImageArtifact (typename org.dxos.type.image) —
    either generated (remote `url` + provenance) or uploaded (a `file`
    blob). Exactly one of `url` / `file` is populated. Note: generated URLs
    are ephemeral and may expire; upload a file or re-materialize for
    permanence.
  fields:
    url?: string                # remote image URL (Format.URL annotation); generated images
    file?: Ref<File.File>       # uploaded image blob (via the file uploader)
    prompt?: string             # resolved / magic prompt actually used
    model?: string              # provider model id (e.g. ideogram V_2)
    resolution?: string         # e.g. "1024x1024"
    seed?: number
    styleType?: string
    isImageSafe?: boolean
    metadata?: Record<string, unknown>   # provider-specific extras
```

```mdl
type ImageArtifact
  desc: >
    Root ECHO object (typename org.dxos.type.imageArtifact). Pairs an
    editable prompt with the images generated for / uploaded to it.
  fields:
    name?: string
    instructions: Ref<Instructions>       # prompt body lives in Instructions.text (Ref<Text>)
    images: Ref<Image>[]                  # ordered generated + uploaded images
  factory:
    # make() creates a child Instructions (which owns a Text body) and
    # parents it to the artifact so it cascade-deletes / deep-clones.
```

```mdl
type Gallery
  desc: >
    An ordered collection of Images that it OWNS (typename org.dxos.type.gallery).
    Each image is parented to the gallery (cascade-delete / deep-clone). Unlike
    ImageArtifact it has no prompt — images are added by upload.
  fields:
    name?: string
    images: Ref<Image>[]                  # owned images (parented on add)
```

```mdl
type ImageGenerationRequest
  desc: Provider-agnostic generation request (Effect Schema in ImageCapabilities).
  fields:
    prompt: string
    negativePrompt?: string
    aspectRatio?: string        # e.g. "1x1", "16x9"
    model?: string
    styleType?: string
    seed?: number
    count?: number              # number of images to generate (default 1)
```

```mdl
type GeneratedImageData
  desc: One image entry in a generation result (before it becomes an Image).
  fields:
    url: string
    prompt?: string
    model?: string
    resolution?: string
    seed?: number
    styleType?: string
    isImageSafe?: boolean
    metadata?: Record<string, unknown>
```

```mdl
type ImageGenerationResult
  fields:
    images: GeneratedImageData[]
```

```mdl
type ImageGenerationService
  desc: >
    The image-creation abstraction. Contributed by provider plugins via
    Capability.contributes(ImageCapabilities.ImageGenerationService,
    [service]) and resolved (by id, else first) by the generateImage op.
    generate() is credential-agnostic: the op resolves the API key from
    the Connector-managed AccessToken (via CredentialsService keyed by
    `source`) and passes it in. `source` is undefined for keyless
    providers (e.g. the test mock).
  fields:
    id: string                  # e.g. "ideogram"
    label: string               # e.g. "Ideogram"
    source?: string             # AccessToken.source for the credential (e.g. "ideogram.ai")
    connectorId?: string        # Connection.connectorId; lets the UI render the ConnectorAuth "Connect" button
    generate: (request: ImageGenerationRequest, options: { apiKey?: Redacted<string> }) => Promise<ImageGenerationResult>
  capability:
    # Capability.make<ImageGenerationService>(`${meta.profile.key}.capability.image-generation-service`)
    # (single-service contribution, resolved via Capability.getAll like TripCapabilities.RoutingService)
```

## Operations

```mdl
op generateImage
  desc: >
    Generate images for an ImageArtifact from its prompt and append them.
    Resolves the ImageGenerationService (by `provider`, else the first
    registered), resolves the provider's API key from the
    Connector-managed AccessToken via CredentialsService when
    `service.source` is set, calls service.generate(), and appends an
    Image per result to artifact.images.
  input:
    artifact: Ref<ImageArtifact>
    provider?: string           # ImageGenerationService.id; default = first registered
    count?: number              # number of images to generate (default 1)
  output:
    count: number               # number of images appended
  errors:
    - NoImageGenerationService — no provider registered (or none matching `provider`).
    - MissingCredential — provider needs a `source` credential but none is connected.
    - GenerationError — bubbled provider failure.
  services:
    - Database.Service
    - Capability.Service
    - CredentialsService
  effects: [echo:write]
  behavior:
    - Load the artifact and its instructions; read the prompt from
      instructions.text (Ref<Text>).
    - Pick the service; if service.source set, apiKey =
      CredentialsService.getCredential({ service: service.source }).apiKey.
    - Build the ImageGenerationRequest from the prompt (+ artifact options
      later); await service.generate(request, { apiKey }).
    - For each result, Image.make({ url, … }) and push Ref.make(image)
      onto artifact.images.
```

## Components

```mdl
component ImageArtifactArticle
  desc: >
    Main article surface for an ImageArtifact. Panel + Toolbar (tabs) with
    the prompt below and the selected image (or the gallery) below that.
  props:
    role: string
    subject: ImageArtifact
    attendableId?: string
  state:
    selected: 'all' | number    # 'all' → gallery; number → single image index
    generating: boolean
  actions:
    generate()                  # invokes op:generateImage; shows generating state
    upload()                    # opens a file picker; uploads via useFileUpload → file-backed Image
    select(tab: 'all' | number)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [All] [1] [2] [3] …        [Upload] [Generate]   │  ← Toolbar tabs + upload + connect/generate
    ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ prompt: a serene mountain lake at dawn …          │  ← Instructions prompt (editable)
    ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │                                                  │
    │            selected image                        │  ← single image, or…
    │        (or Masonry gallery for "All")            │  ← vendored ImageGallery
    │                                                  │
    └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
  notes:
    - When the resolved provider has a `connectorId` and no matching Connection
      exists, the Generate slot renders the provider's `ConnectorAuth` surface
      ("Connect …") instead of the Generate button.
```

```mdl
component PromptEditor
  desc: >
    Renders and edits the ImageArtifact's prompt (the Instructions Text body),
    live-bound to the Text object via useTextEditor.
  props:
    id: string
    text?: Text.Text
```

```mdl
component ImageView
  desc: A single Image (generated URL or uploaded file) plus its provenance metadata.
  props:
    image?: { url?; file?: Ref<File.File>; prompt?; model?; resolution?; seed? }
```

```mdl
component GalleryArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface for a Gallery: a masonry of its owned images with a toolbar to add (upload)
    images and delete the multi-selected ones. Selection state is owned here via `useListSelection`
    (multi, from @dxos/react-ui-list); the masonry renders the outline and emits tile clicks.
  props:
    role: string
    subject: Gallery
  state:
    selectedIds: ReadonlySet<string>      # keyed by Image.id
  actions:
    addImage()                            # upload → file-backed Image parented to the gallery
    deleteSelected()                      # remove selected refs + db.remove the owned Images
    toggle(id)                            # bind(id).toggle() from useListSelection
```

## Cross-package additions

### Vendored gallery (from plugin-gallery)

`plugin-image` vendors a masonry gallery (`ImageGallery`) adapted from
`plugin-gallery`'s `Lightbox` (`@dxos/react-ui-masonry` grid of `GalleryImage`
cards), plus the `useImageUrl` + `useFileUpload` hooks, so no `Gallery` ECHO
object is required. Each tile resolves its own source via `useImageSource`
(remote `url`, else the uploaded file's `data:`/`blob:` URL). plugin-gallery
is deleted (see the scope table).

```mdl
type ImageSource (plugin-image/hooks)
  desc: A gallery item — a remote URL and/or an uploaded File.File ref.
  fields:
    url?: string
    file?: Ref<File.File>
    name?: string

component ImageGallery (plugin-image, vendored)
  desc: >
    Masonry of images. Each tile calls useImageSource(item) → src (url, else
    loaded-file blob) and renders a presentation-only GalleryImage. Lives in
    src/components (no app-framework deps). Forwards selection to the masonry.
  props:
    images: ReadonlyArray<ImageSource>    # ImageSource gains an `id` (the Image id) used as key + selection id
    emptyMessage?: ReactNode
    selectedIds?: ReadonlySet<string>
    onSelect?: (id, event) => void
```

### @dxos/react-ui-masonry — selection support (detour)

`Masonry.Viewport` gained optional `selectedIds?: ReadonlySet<string>` +
`onSelect?: (id, event) => void`: selected tiles render an inset ring +
`aria-selected`, clicking a tile emits `onSelect`, and the `Tile` receives a
`selected` prop. Masonry stays low-level — selection STATE (single/multi) is
owned by the consumer, following `@dxos/react-ui-list`'s `useListSelection`
pattern (the `Gallery` article uses it in `multi` mode). Additive + backward
compatible.

### plugin-ideogram — provider + connector (headless)

Summarized here; authoritative in `plugin-ideogram/PLUGIN.mdl`.

```mdl
feat IdeogramProvider
  desc: >
    Headless plugin. (1) Registers a Connector entry (source "ideogram.ai",
    API-key credential form) so the user can connect Ideogram through the
    generic Connector UI; the token is stored as an AccessToken +
    Connection in ECHO. (2) Contributes an ImageGenerationService whose
    generate() POSTs https://api.ideogram.ai/generate with header
    `Api-Key: <token>` and maps the response `data[]` to
    GeneratedImageData. No React/UI dependencies.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Author prompt

  req F-1.1: An ImageArtifact opens in an article surface showing its prompt (Instructions text) editable below the toolbar.
  req F-1.2: Edits to the prompt persist to the Instructions Text body reactively.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Generate images

  req F-2.1:
    when: user clicks Generate
    then: op:generateImage runs against the resolved ImageGenerationService and appends the produced GeneratedImage(s) to artifact.images.

  req F-2.2:
    when: the resolved provider declares a `source` but no matching credential is connected
    then: generation fails with MissingCredential (surfaced to the user); no images are appended.

  req F-2.3:
    when: no ImageGenerationService is registered
    then: the Generate action is disabled.

  req F-2.4:
    when: the resolved provider has a `connectorId` and no matching Connection exists
    then: the toolbar shows the provider's `ConnectorAuth` "Connect …" surface in place of Generate.
```

```mdl
feat F-Upload: Upload images

  req F-U.1:
    when: user clicks Upload
    then: a file picker opens (image/*); each selected file is uploaded via the
          FileUploader capability and appended as a file-backed Image.
  req F-U.2:
    when: no FileUploader backend is registered
    then: the Upload action is disabled.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Review images via toolbar tabs

  req F-3.1: The toolbar shows one tab per image (generated or uploaded) plus an "All" tab.
  req F-3.2:
    when: user selects a numbered image tab
    then: that single image is shown with its provenance metadata.
  req F-3.3:
    when: user selects the "All" tab
    then: all images render in the vendored masonry gallery (URLs + uploaded file blobs).
  req F-3.4: With no images yet, only the "All" tab is shown (empty state).
```

```mdl
feat F-Gallery: Gallery article (masonry + multi-select)

  req F-G.1: A Gallery opens in an article showing its owned images in a masonry.
  req F-G.2:
    when: user clicks the Add (upload) toolbar button
    then: selected image files upload and are appended as file-backed Images owned by the gallery.
  req F-G.3:
    when: user clicks image tiles
    then: they toggle multi-selection (masonry shows an outline + check on selected tiles).
  req F-G.4:
    when: user clicks Delete with a non-empty selection
    then: the selected Images are removed from the gallery and deleted from the space; selection clears.
  req F-G.5: The Delete toolbar button is disabled when nothing is selected.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Generate appends images (mock provider)
  given: an ImageArtifact with a prompt; a mock ImageGenerationService registered (source undefined)
  when: op:generateImage is invoked
  then:
    - service.generate is called with the prompt
    - artifact.images gains one Image per result, each carrying the returned url + metadata
    - output.count equals the number appended
```

```mdl
test T-1b: Credential plumbing
  given: an ImageArtifact; a provider with source "ideogram.ai"; a connected credential (apiKey)
  when: op:generateImage is invoked
  then: service.generate receives the resolved apiKey (Redacted) and an Image is appended
```

```mdl
test T-2: Missing credential
  given: an ImageArtifact; a provider whose source is "ideogram.ai"; no connected credential
  when: op:generateImage is invoked
  then: it fails with MissingCredential and appends nothing
```

```mdl
test T-3: No provider registered
  given: an ImageArtifact; no ImageGenerationService registered
  then: the Generate toolbar action is disabled
```

```mdl
test T-4: Tabs switch views
  given: an ImageArtifact with 3 images open in an article
  when: user selects the tab for image 2
  then: only image 2 (and its metadata) is shown
  when: user selects the "All" tab
  then: all 3 images render in the gallery
```

```mdl
test T-5: Gallery renders URL + uploaded images
  given: ImageGallery given images = [{ url }, { file: Ref<File.File> }]
  then: both render; the URL item uses its url directly, the file item resolves
        its blob via useImageSource / useImageUrl
```

```mdl
test T-6: Upload appends a file-backed Image
  given: an ImageArtifact; a registered FileUploader backend
  when: user uploads an image file
  then: artifact.images gains an Image whose `file` refs the uploaded File.File
```

## Out of scope (v1)

- Auto-materializing generated URLs into File.File blobs for permanence
  (generated URLs are ephemeral; users can upload for a durable copy).
- Multi-account credential selection / an in-artifact connection picker;
  the first matching connected credential is used.
- Editing / upscaling / remixing existing images, image-to-image, and
  reference-image inputs.
- Prompt options UI (aspect ratio, model, style, seed, count) beyond the
  prompt text; the request schema reserves the fields.
- AI-skill / agent tool exposure of generateImage.
